# Pagination & Filtering Rules

**Note:** This rule provides specific pagination patterns. All implementations must follow `nestjs-architecture.mdc` section 6 for data access patterns.

## Pagination

All list endpoints must support pagination:
- Query parameters: `page` (default: 1), `pageSize` (default: 20, max: 100)
- Response format: `{ count, next, previous, results }`

## Pagination DTO

Extend DTO with pagination fields (use `ApiProperty` for Swagger when applicable):

```typescript
@ApiProperty({ required: false, default: 1, minimum: 1 })
@IsOptional()
@Type(() => Number)
@IsNumber()
@Min(1)
page?: number = 1;

@ApiProperty({ required: false, default: 20, minimum: 1, maximum: 100 })
@IsOptional()
@Type(() => Number)
@IsNumber()
@Min(1)
@Max(100)
pageSize?: number = 20;
```

For endpoints with only pagination (no filters): create a DTO that extends or includes these fields, e.g. `GetProposalsByRequestDto`.

## Response Format

`PaginationResult<T>` from `src/common/utils/pagination.util`:

```typescript
{
  count: number;
  next: string | null;      // relative URL, e.g. "/api/requests?page=2&pageSize=20"
  previous: string | null;  // relative URL or null
  results: T[];
}
```

## PaginationUtil

Use static methods from `PaginationUtil`:
- `PaginationUtil.normalizePage(dto.page)` — returns 1 if invalid
- `PaginationUtil.normalizePageSize(dto.pageSize)` — clamps to 1–100, default 20
- `PaginationUtil.getSkip(page, pageSize)` — `(page - 1) * pageSize`
- `PaginationUtil.createPaginationResult(results, count, page, pageSize, baseUrl, queryParams?)` — builds response with `next`/`previous` URLs

`baseUrl` — full relative path (e.g. `/api/requests` or `/api/proposals/requests/:requestId`).
`queryParams` — object to include in next/previous URLs (e.g. `dto` or `{ page, pageSize }`).

## Filtering

- Filter through query parameters in DTO
- Support multiple filters simultaneously
- Use Mongoose query methods (`FilterQuery<T>` when possible)
- Use `$regex` with `$options: 'i'` for case-insensitive text search on `title` and `description`

## Sorting

Use `SortUtil.buildSortObject(dto.sort)` from `src/common/utils/sort.util`:
- `sort=createdAt` — ASC
- `sort=-createdAt` — DESC (prefix `-` for descending)
- Fallback: `{ createdAt: -1 }` when no sort or invalid

## Search

Current implementation uses `$regex` (not `$text`):

```typescript
if (dto.search) {
  query.$or = [
    { title: { $regex: dto.search, $options: 'i' } },
    { description: { $regex: dto.search, $options: 'i' } },
  ];
}
```

For full-text search, consider MongoDB text indexes or Atlas Search.

## Implementation Pattern

```typescript
async findAll(dto: GetXxxDto): Promise<PaginationResult<FormattedXxx>> {
  const page = PaginationUtil.normalizePage(dto.page);
  const pageSize = PaginationUtil.normalizePageSize(dto.pageSize);
  const skip = PaginationUtil.getSkip(page, pageSize);

  const query: FilterQuery<XxxDocument> = { /* build from dto */ };

  const sortObj = SortUtil.buildSortObject(dto.sort);
  const sort = (sortObj ?? { createdAt: -1 }) as Record<string, 1 | -1>;

  const results = await this.xxxModel
    .find(query)
    .populate(/* ... */)
    .sort(sort)
    .skip(skip)
    .limit(pageSize)
    .lean()
    .exec();

  const count = await this.xxxModel.countDocuments(query).exec();

  return PaginationUtil.createPaginationResult(
    results,
    count,
    page,
    pageSize,
    '/api/xxx',
    dto,
  );
}
```

For nested resources (e.g. proposals by request):

```typescript
const baseUrl = `/api/proposals/requests/${requestId}`;
return PaginationUtil.createPaginationResult(
  results,
  count,
  page,
  pageSize,
  baseUrl,
  { page, pageSize },
);
```
